From cdbf750d977d398aafc83234f26b66469c0b82f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 09:34:20 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 7: route Anthropic calls through main to bypass
 renderer CORS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Custom Anthropic-compatible endpoints (corporate gateways, e.g.
Datadog) typically don't return permissive CORS headers, so the
renderer's fetch() to /v1/messages was failing CORS preflight
before the response body was reachable.

Adds IKrtAiClient (mirroring the IGhClient main/renderer split):
  - common/krt.ts: interface + request/response shapes.
  - electron-main/aiClientMainService.ts: Node fetch in main.
  - electron-browser/krtAiClient.ts: ProxyChannel binding.
  - app.ts: registers the krt:ai channel alongside krt:gh.

TourGenerator now POSTs through the IPC client instead of fetching
directly. Drops the anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access
header — irrelevant from main-process Node.
